			</text>
		</textBlock>
		<textBlock>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="In this activity, you will determine how and in what ways community members will be engaged in the ERB process.">
			</text>
		</textBlock>
		<textBlock>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Bold"
			text="Why do this: ">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="It is important to consider the type of engagement that is appropriate for your project. Different types of engagement have different levels of involvement by community members and different expectations for the impact of that involvement on decision making (see ">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Hyperlink"
			text="figure"
			linkType="externalDOC"
			link="figure_23.png">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="). More intensive engagement may require more time and effort, however, that effort can pay off with improved trust and relationships and more actionable results.">
			</text>
		</textBlock>
		<textBlock>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Bold"
			text="How to do this: ">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="Core team will meet to review the opportunities for engagement throughout the ERB process. The team will discuss specific considerations of underrepresented groups in your community and how you might invite them to the table. Then the team will record how different audiences should be engaged throughout the ERB process in column 'E' of the ">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Hyperlink"
			text="Community Connections Table"
			linkType="externalDOC"
			link="Ch2_Community_Connections_Table.docx">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
